oai_dc:dc.dc:title: James Alexander Cathey Milliken ambrotype
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Ambrotype of James Alexander "Alec" Cathey Milliken (April 3, 1836-September 20, 1920), Co. K, 1st Tenn. Inf. (Turney's) Regt., CSA. Milliken enlisted on April 29, 1861. He was detailed as a medical sergeant under Dr. Calvin McGuire and worked in this capacity during the Second Battle of Manassas. On his pension application, Milliken states he was involved in the battles of Seven Pines, Fredericksburg, Manassas, Cedar Mountain, Antietam, Harpers Ferry, and Gettysburg.
